{
  "stem": "14613.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But there were a number of rooms so that considering the situation in Poland, I think it was considered a very nice house.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's a-- it's a lot of misleading statement about the, the, the the rich Jews in Poland, which is very misleading because, by and large, there was only a small percentage of Jews that were well off.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I would say the majority of Jews in Poland were the middle- or low-middle- or poor class.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] so that-- even to the schools that we went, which was the Jewish gymnasium, the people that were well-off, they had to pay for it, which was quite expensive.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never thought about as far as the neighborhood that I lived in.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I, I, I think I would say, it was a mixed neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Although when I think about it, most of the people in our building, I believe they were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But around us there were also Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that it was not-- at least, the district that I lived in, it was not what you could call a 'ghetto.' A ghetto was when we were in later on during the war.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this was not a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, but to a very, very small extent.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We basically-- my friends were the friends from school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And inasmuch as I went to a private school-- I did not go to a public school, which was mixed Jews and Gentiles.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Our school was the Jewish gymnasium, which was strictly [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] for Jewish people because we studied the Hebrew and Polish.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that my friends were, really, the friends from my school.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And such, they were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father certainly did business with non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
